      "weather": "Overcast",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STIFLER (1) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 2.5 lengths at Murray Bridge Straight in a handy 16.80 beating Lenny's Honey. Can make it two on the bounce. BINNAWAY PEARL (8) scored by 1.75 lengths last time (16.56) in a Special conditions race over 300m at this track. Boasts a top strike-rate from this draw, winning six of 10 runs. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. GALBA STACEY (4) generally flies the lids but last time was always well back and ran below best, finishing fifth (20.16) in a Grade 4/5 at Angle Park. Fast away and won (20.16) at Angle Park the start prior. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and two minor placings from five starts. One of the better chances.",
